Predicting Employee Attrition in the Workplace
========================================================
author: Agatha North
date: 12/03/2017
autosize: true
css: custom.css
type: exclaim

Overview
========================================================
type: exclaim

- High employee attrition is both costly and inefficent

- Using the App Happyforce to collect data allows predictive measures to anticipate and ideally prevent the loss of valuable employees

- The data, although valuable, may be less practical than companies using more corperate and readily accessable data from within

Data Wrangling
========================================================
type: exclaim

Data wrangling was broken down into three sections
- Cleaning the dates and assigning the companies a unique id

- Scrutinizing the data to determine which companies needed to be removed

- Creating a new dataset that organized the data into variables about specific employees, rather than companies

Statistical Analysis
========================================================
type: exclaim

![alt text](RplotComp.png)
***
Each company has its own culture, and some of this is reflected in their votes. Comparing C12 and C33 for example, gives the impression of two very different workplaces. This data was extremely helpful in predicting churning, based simply around representing the company's unique culture and firing policy.

